# Privacy Policy for HARK

Last updated: April 29, 2026

## Data Collection
HARK does not collect, store, or transmit any user data to external servers.

## Local Storage
The extension stores user preferences (capture pattern, HTTP method filters, settings) locally using chrome.storage.local API. This data never leaves your device.

## Network Activity
HARK monitors network requests only when explicitly activated by the user on a specific tab. All captured data is saved locally to your Downloads folder. No data is sent to any external service.

## Third Parties
HARK does not share data with any third parties because it does not collect any data.

## Contact
For questions about this privacy policy, please open an issue at: https://github.com/MsArk/hark-extension/issues
